## Ingredients

Shortbread 
- 1/2 cup of packed brown sugar
- 2 teaspoons of vanilla extract (I used imitation)
- 2 teaspoons of fine sea salt 
- 1 cup melted butter
- 2+1/2 cups of AP flour
- 1 tablespoon of freshly ground/ blended aniseed (Optional once dough is ready)

Caramel 
- 1/2 cup butter
- A 14 ounce can of sweetened condensed milk 
- 1 cup of packed brown sugar
- 1/2 cup of dark corn-syrup
- 1 teaspoon of salt


## Directions

Shortbread 
1. Preheat oven to 350¬∞f
2. Cream together the brown sugar, salt, vanilla, and melted butter
3. Add in the flour and bring together with spoon or by hand until a ‚Äúwet sand‚Äù texture is achieved
4. Add a tablespoon of freshly ground aniseed (optional)
5. Line 10x18‚Äù baking tray with aluminum (go over the edges)
6. Now firmly press the crumbly dough into the tray making sure it‚Äôs even 
7. Use a fork to poke many many air holes into the dough after it‚Äôs all pressed 
8. Place into the preheated oven for 17-22mins 
9. Once finished allow it to fully cool to room temp without removing from the pan

Carmel
1. While it cools melt a half cup of butter in a small pot or saucepan at medium heat 
2. Then add the sweetened condensed milk, the corn syrup, brown sugar, and salt all at once to the butter
3. Use a whisk to combine the ingredients and continuously whisk till the Carmel hits about 236¬∞ or for about 15-20 minutes or till the Carmel reaches consistency of choice
4. Once it‚Äôs ready quickly pour and then evenly spread over the room temp shortbread that‚Äôs still in the pan
5. Allow it to sit and fully cook as well before moving on to the Chocolate 

Chocolate 
1. Rough Chop the dark chocolate and add to a bowl with the semisweet chocolate chips
2. Ready a double boiler over medium or what ever method you prefer
3. Add the chocolate and constantly fold till it‚Äôs combined and fully melted
4. Now pour and spread onto the caramel layer 
5. Let rest in the fridge over night before cutting 

